OL,3,CInside the salon where hairdressers
OL,4,Care trained to spot domestic abuse
OL,5,Csigns
OL,7,FHairdressers at a salon in Devon have
OL,8,Fbecome to first to train in spotting
OL,9,Fsigns of domestic abuse.
OL,11,FThe team at Meraki Salon in Exeter was
OL,12,Ftrained by the charity FearFree, as
OL,13,Fpart of its new 'Combing Together'
OL,14,Fprogramme.
OL,16,FThe charity says that for many victims
OL,17,Fof abuse, hairdressers, barbers and
OL,18,Fbeauty salons are the ideal setting to
OL,19,Fopen up with someone they trust.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/7
