OL,3,CInside the salon where hairdressers
OL,4,Care trained to spot domestic abuse
OL,5,Csigns
OL,7,FHayley Williams, owner of Meraki, said
OL,8,Fthe training has given her staff the
OL,9,Fconfidence navigate more challenging
OL,10,Fconversations with their clients.
OL,12,FHayley said: "We now know what to say,
OL,13,Fwhat not to say, and how to signpost
OL,14,Fguests in the right direction to get
OL,15,Fhelp.
OL,17,F"We're not just here to cut hair, I
OL,18,Fbelieve we're here as listeners as
OL,19,Fconfidants and also we can be
OL,20,Flifelines so I do feel like we have
OL,21,Fthe potential to make a difference."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
