OL,3,CInside the salon where hairdressers
OL,4,Care trained to spot domestic abuse
OL,5,Csigns
OL,7,F"Barbershops are a really common place
OL,8,Ffor men to attend and quite
OL,9,Ffrequently. We see the relationships
OL,10,Fthat professionals have with their
OL,11,Fclients, it's really built on trust.
OL,13,F"It's also important that
OL,14,Fprofessionals feel comfortable in
OL,15,Fapproaching the situation because we
OL,16,Fdon't want them to go home feeling
OL,17,Fthat's their burden."
OL,19,FHolly Tarr, who is a hairdresser at
OL,20,FMeraki, has trained in spotting signs
OL,21,Fof domestic abuse.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
